kind.prompt:
You are implementing a university course catalog Blazor Web App. The project has already been scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-2db08c14cb6842648f55cb7b3800e2dc/UniversityCourseCatalog` using `dotnet new blazor -int Server --no-https`. It's Interactive Server per-page (pages are static SSR by default, opt-in to InteractiveServer).

## Requirements
- Browse departments and courses in a searchable, filterable list
- View course detail pages (description, schedule, credits, instructor bio)
- Students submit an enrollment request form (name, student ID, course selection) — standard HTML form, no wizards or real-time validation
- Homepage shows featured courses and department links
- No authentication
- Intranet with fast connectivity

## Architecture Decisions
- **Static SSR** for: Home, CourseDetail, Enroll, EnrollConfirmation pages (no interactivity needed)
- **Interactive Server** for: Courses list page only (needs live search/filter without full page reloads)
- Use in-memory sample data via a singleton service (no database)
- Standard HTML forms with `[SupplyParameterFromForm]` for the enrollment form

## What to implement

### 1. Models — Create `/tmp/sv-2db08c14cb6842648f55cb7b3800e2dc/UniversityCourseCatalog/Models/` directory with:

**Department.cs**
```csharp
namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class Department
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Code { get; set; } = ""; // e.g. "CS", "MATH"
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
}
```

**Course.cs**
```csharp
namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class Course
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string Title { get; set; } = "";
    public string CourseCode { get; set; } = ""; // e.g. "CS 101"
    public string Description { get; set; } = "";
    public int Credits { get; set; }
    public string Schedule { get; set; } = ""; // e.g. "MWF 10:00-10:50 AM"
    public string Location { get; set; } = "";
    public int DepartmentId { get; set; }
    public string DepartmentName { get; set; } = "";
    public string DepartmentCode { get; set; } = "";
    public Instructor Instructor { get; set; } = new();
    public bool IsFeatured { get; set; }
    public int MaxEnrollment { get; set; }
    public int CurrentEnrollment { get; set; }
}
```

**Instructor.cs**
```csharp
namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class Instructor
{
    public string Name { get; set; } = "";
    public string Title { get; set; } = ""; // e.g. "Associate Professor"
    public string Bio { get; set; } = "";
    public string Email { get; set; } = "";
    public string Office { get; set; } = "";
}
```

**EnrollmentRequest.cs**
```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations;

namespace UniversityCourseCatalog.Models;

public class EnrollmentRequest
{
    [Required(ErrorMessage = "Name is required.")]
    [StringLength(100)]
    public string StudentName { get; set; } = "";

    [Required(ErrorMessage = "Student ID is required.")]
    [RegularExpression(@"^[A-Z]{1}\d{7}$", ErrorMessage = "Student ID must be a letter followed by 7 digits (e.g., S1234567).")]
    public string StudentId { get; set; } = "";

    [Required(ErrorMessage = "Please select a course.")]
    [Range(1, int.MaxValue, ErrorMessage = "Please select a course.")]
    public int CourseId { get; set; }
}
```

### 2. Services — Create `/tmp/sv-2db08c14cb6842648f55cb7b3800e2dc/UniversityCourseCatalog/Services/CatalogService.cs`

Create a `CatalogService` class registered as singleton. It should hold in-memory lists of departments and courses with realistic sample data.

Departments (at least 5): Computer Science (CS), Mathematics (MATH), Physics (PHYS), English (ENGL), History (HIST)

Courses: At least 3-4 per department with realistic titles, descriptions, schedules, instructors with bios, credit hours (3-4), varied schedules (MWF, TTh patterns), location (building + room). Mark 4-5 courses as IsFeatured.

Methods:
- `IReadOnlyList<Department> GetDepartments()`
- `Department? GetDepartment(int id)`
- `IReadOnlyList<Course> GetCourses()`
- `IReadOnlyList<Course> GetCoursesByDepartment(int departmentId)`
- `IReadOnlyList<Course> SearchCourses(string? searchTerm, int? departmentId, int? credits)` — filter by title/code/description text match, department, and credits
- `Course? GetCourse(int id)`
- `IReadOnlyList<Course> GetFeaturedCourses()`
- `void SubmitEnrollment(EnrollmentRequest request)` — just stores in a list (no real processing)

### 3. Register service in Program.cs

Add `builder.Services.AddSingleton<UniversityCourseCatalog.Services.CatalogService>();` before `var app = builder.Build();`.

### 4. Delete template pages

Delete these template files:
- `Components/Pages/Counter.razor`
- `Components/Pages/Weather.razor`
- `Components/Pages/Error.razor` — keep this if it exists, it's the error page
- `Components/Layout/NavMenu.razor`
- `Components/Layout/NavMenu.razor.css`

### 5. Create new NavMenu — `Components/Layout/NavMenu.razor`

Simple top navigation bar (no sidebar). Links: Home, Courses, Enroll. University name "Westfield University" as brand.

